<body>
    <h1>BlockingLimitation</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <div class=3D"contentLayout2">=20
<div class=3D"columnLayout two-right-sidebar" data-layout=3D"two-right-side=
bar">=20
<div class=3D"cell normal" data-type=3D"normal">=20
<div class=3D"innerCell">=20
<p>A generic Limitation type to use when no other Limitation has been imple=
mented. Without any limitation assigned, a LimitationNotFoundException is t=
hrown.</p>
<p>It is called "blocking" because it will always tell the permissions syst=
em that the User does not have access to any Policy it is assigned to, maki=
ng the permissions system move on to the next Policy.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class=3D"highlight-grey confluenceTd" data-highlight-colour=3D"grey">Id=
entifier</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><code>n/a</code> (configured for <code>ezjscore<=
/code> limitation <code> FunctionList</code> out of the box)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"highlight-grey confluenceTd" data-highlight-colour=3D"grey">Va=
lue Class</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><code>eZ\Publish\API\Repository\Values\User\Limi=
tation\BlockingLimitation</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"highlight-grey confluenceTd" colspan=3D"1" data-highlight-colo=
ur=3D"grey">Type Class</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><code>eZ\Publish\Core\Limitation\B=
lockingLimitationType</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"highlight-grey confluenceTd" colspan=3D"1" data-highlight-colo=
ur=3D"grey">Criterion used</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">MatchNone</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"highlight-grey confluenceTd" colspan=3D"1" data-highlight-colo=
ur=3D"grey">Role Limitation</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">no</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
